which computes an absolute Unix timestamp that drifts — use a stable reset time computed at response time, not derived from Date.now(\",\"scope\":\"src/middleware/rateLimit.ts\"},{\"kind\":\"lesson\",\"text\":\"Always verify newly exported helpers (like `byApiKey`) are covered by tests before merging; untested exports are easy to miss in diff review.\",\"scope\":\"src/middleware/rateLimit.test.ts\"},{\"kind\":\"convention\",\"text\":\"Middleware uses a factory pattern: `createXxxMiddleware()` returning a handler, with a paired `XxxConfig` interface and X-RateLimit-* + 429+Retry-After response shape.\",\"scope\":\"src/middleware\"},{\"kind\":\"convention\",\"text\":\"Test files use `describe/it/expect/vi`, `afterEach` with `vi.useRealTimers()`, a `NextRequest` factory helper, and call `limiter.destroy()` for cleanup.\",\"scope\":\"*.test.ts\"}]}","createdAt":"2026-04-18T13:01:41.482Z","wordCount":937,"positions":[2,10,19,32,39,48,57,67,73,80,87,92,100,116,128,140,149,154,169,178,184,191,197,202,214,223,229,233,246,251,258,266,270,281,291,298,305,314,321,328,335,341,350,359,365,380,391,397,404,413,422,434,442,450,455,465,473,477,488,498,503,510,517,530,537,548,555,563,573,596,608,624,632,643,659,673,677,683,689,698,707,715,719,734,741,754,761,766,772,777,789,796,802,819,822,843,856,864,876,882,890,905,916,926,931]}},"totalDocs":7}